Title: Traversable Wormholes and Black Hole Complementarity

Authors: Daniel Gottesman

Comments: 4 pages, CALT-68-1931

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D51 (1995) 4600-4602

Black hole complementarity is incompatible with the existence of traversablewormholes. In fact, traversable wormholes cause problems for any theory whereinformation comes out in the Hawking radiation.